The paper proposes a deep learning model for predicting human eye fixations, which falls under the domain of computer vision and neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The model is based on a fully convolutional neural network, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the model on eye fixation datasets, which indicates that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
